-- Rio Tinto Forms Joint Mining Venture With Kazakh State-Run Tau-Ken Samruk
-- Nariman Gizitdinov
-- 2010-06-30T06:59:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/rio-tinto-forms-joint-mining-venture-with-kazakh-state-run-tau-ken-samruk.html

          
          
             Rio Tinto Group, the world’s third-
largest mining company, created a 50-50 venture with
Kazakhstan’s state-owned Tau-Ken Samruk to tap the Central Asian
nation’s mineral reserves.  
 The venture will explore for copper, gold, bauxite and iron
ore, Bolat Svyatov, chief executive officer of Tau-Ken Samruk,
said today in the Kazakh capital, Astana. Tau-Ken Samruk is a
mining unit of Kazakhstan National Wellbeing Fund Samruk-Kazyna.  
